- VSCode Version: 1.11.2
- OS Version: OSX

```ts
abstract class Foo {
  options: {
    x: string
  }
}

class Koo extends Foo { // already know options is missing x
  options = {
    // should get `x` as property
  }
  do() {
    this.options = {
      // does recognize `x` as property
    }
  }
}
```

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3254987/25303098/dd4f1864-2700-11e7-83d4-c32ea155bc26.png)

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3254987/25303091/ce5143fa-2700-11e7-801a-cf3eea2a9d10.png)

Following is the code :
```
let config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration();
let keyValue: string = "";
let hasValue: boolean = config.has(key);
keyValue = config.get<null>(key, null);
if (keyValue != "") {
    customSettings.ignoreUploadSettings[key] = keyValue;
    keysUpdated.push(config.update(key, undefined, true));
}
```


When i dont have any setting present say, `editor.wordWrap` 
i always get `config.has(key)` as `true` instead of `false`
also 
`config.get<null>(key, null)` as `""` instead of `null`
